      ],
      "source": "https://www.cityneighborhoods.nyc/mott-haven"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The 1905 Carnegie‑funded Mott Haven Branch Library is New York City’s first public library in the Bronx.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mott_Haven%2C_Bronx"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Harlem River Railroad (1842) and Third Avenue Elevated Line (1887) linked Mott Haven to Manhattan, making it a factory hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.cityneighborhoods.nyc/mott-haven"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Alexander Avenue runs through the historic district and was named for Alexander Bathgate, overseer of the Morris manor.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
